KwaZulu-Natal Premier Sihle Zikalala will update the media on what the relaxation of the lockdown means for the province as well as other issues on the Covid-19 epidemic. DURBAN - KwaZulu-Natal Premier Sihle Zikalala will on Sunday afternoon give an update on the coronavirus pandemic in the province. The provincial government says the KZN Command Team met on Friday after President Cyril Ramaphosa announced a low risk-adjusted approach to relax the lockdown. On 1 May the country will move from the current level 5 to level 4. Zikalala will update the media on what the relaxation of the lockdown means for the province as well as other issues on the COVID-19 epidemic. KwaZulu Natal has recorded the third-highest number of infections in the country. READ: SA looking at borrowing R95bn for COVID-19 The province has 847 confirmed coronavirus cases with 29 deaths and  241 recoveries. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.